title: My 3D Printer Paid For Itself in 2 Days.

media:group.media:title: My 3D Printer Paid For Itself in 2 Days.
media:group.media:description: Wall mounted arms for for Studio lights are REDICULOUSLY expensive! I figured out how to modify my existing tripods to do the job. I used a Focoos Odin 5 S3 printer to make the parts and that printer currently costs $350. Coincidentally that is the cost that I would have spent on 4 of these light arms if I didn't have the DIY running through my veins.
